## Task 4 — Web Server Access Logs Analysis

### Apache access log fields

A line from `/var/log/apache2/access.log` breaks down as:

```
172.16.0.1 - - [06/Jun/2024:13:58:44] "GET / HTTP/1.1" 200 "-" "Mozilla/5.0 ..."
```

| Field | Example | Meaning |
|-------|---------|---------|
| IP Address | `172.16.0.1` | Who made the request |
| Timestamp | `[06/Jun/2024:13:58:44]` | When |
| HTTP Method | `GET` / `POST` | Action requested |
| URL | `/contact` | Resource requested |
| Status Code | `200`, `404`, `500` | Server response |
| User-Agent | `Mozilla/5.0 ...` | Client OS / browser |

### Tooling

```bash
cat access.log                         # dump full file
cat access1.log access2.log > all.log  # combine rotated logs
grep "192.168.1.1" access.log          # filter by string/IP
less access.log                        # page through (/=search, n/N=next/prev)
```

Log file location on the AttackBox: `/root/Rooms/logs/access.log`

### Questions

**Q1 — IP that made the last GET request to `/contact`?**

```bash
grep "/contact" access.log | grep "GET" | tail -n 1
```
**Answer:** `10.0.0.1` ✅

**Q2 — When was the last POST request made by IP `172.16.0.1`?**

```bash
grep "172.16.0.1" access.log | grep "POST" | tail -n 1
```
**Answer:** `06/Jun/2024:13:55:44` ✅

**Q3 — Based on Q2, to which URL was that POST request made?**

(Read the URL field from the same line as Q2.)
**Answer:** `/contact` ✅

