## Key Takeaways / Cheatsheet

- `grep "<pattern>" file | tail -n 1` → fast way to grab the **last** matching entry.
- Chain `grep` to narrow: `grep IP | grep METHOD`.
- `cat a.log b.log > combined.log` to merge rotated logs before analysis.
- In `less`: `/pattern` to search, `n`/`N` to jump between hits, `space`/`b` to page.
- Status codes worth flagging in an investigation: `401/403` (auth), `404` (recon/scanning), `500` (errors/possible exploitation).

